{{Short description|French marine painter}}
[[File:Carenage d'un voilier-A Aiguier mg 6194.jpg|thumb|right|200px|''Hull repairs on a sail ship''. Oil on canvas, 1846. Now at the Marseille naval museum.]]
'''Louis Auguste Laurent Aiguier''', a French [[Marine art|marine painter]], was born at [[Toulon]] in 1819, and died in that town in 1865. There are examples of his work in the Museums of Toulon and [[Marseille]]s.

